  Abstract                 = {{BACKGROUND}: Assessment of {DNA} integrity and quantity remains a bottleneck for high-throughput molecular genotyping technologies, including next-generation sequencing. In particular, {DNA} extracted from paraffin-embedded tissues, a major potential source of tumor {DNA}, varies widely in quality, leading to unpredictable sequencing data. We describe a picoliter droplet-based digital {PCR} method that enables simultaneous detection of {DNA} integrity and the quantity of amplifiable {DNA}.
