  Abstract                 = {{OBJECTIVES}: Epidermal growth factor receptor ({EGFR}) mutations have been identified in lung adenocarcinomas and are associated with high response chance to {EGFR} tyrosine kinase inhibitors. {EGFR} mutations can be detected in tumour tissue, cytology specimens and blood from lung cancer patients. Thus far, {EGFR} mutation analysis has not been systematically demonstrated for sputum samples. The aim of the present study was to determine whether {EGFR} mutation analysis is attainable on sputum samples, employing different assays in a multicenter study.
