  Abstract                 = {{PURPOSE}: {MicroRNAs} ({miRNAs}) play important roles in the initiation and progression of lung cancer. Measuring {miRNA} expression levels in sputum could provide a potential approach for the diagnosis of lung cancer. The emerging digital {PCR} is a straightforward technique for precise, direct, and absolute quantification of nucleic acids. The objective of the study was to investigate whether digital {PCR} could be used to quantify {miRNAs} in sputum for lung cancer diagnosis.
