  Abstract                 = {{BACKGROUND}: The {EGFR} [epidermal growth factor receptor (erythroblastic leukemia viral (v-erb-b) oncogene homolog, avian)] gene is known to harbor genomic alterations in advanced lung cancer involving gene amplification and kinase mutations that predict the clinical response to {EGFR}-targeted inhibitors. Methods for detecting such molecular changes in lung cancer tumors are desirable.
